<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>

<p>To install Oh My Bash, you can choose between <a href="https://curl.haxx.se/">cURL</a> or <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/">GNU wget</a>, see the commands below:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>If you donâ€™t have cURL installed, use your distributionâ€™s package manager, eg sudo emerge curl # For Gentoo and similar</p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Via cURL</strong>:</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">sh <span class="nt">-c</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="si">$(</span>curl <span class="nt">-fsSL</span> https://raw.github.com/ohmybash/oh-my-bash/master/tools/install.sh<span class="si">)</span><span class="s2">"</span></code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Via wget</strong>:</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">sh <span class="nt">-c</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="si">$(</span>wget https://raw.github.com/ohmybash/oh-my-bash/master/tools/install.sh <span class="nt">-O</span> -<span class="si">)</span><span class="s2">"</span></code></pre></figure>

